---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Hana Code Corp"
  description="Terms of Service for Hana Code Corp and its applications."
>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="section hero">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="effective">Effective Date: March 1, 2026</p>
    </section>
    <section class="section">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using any application or service provided by Hana Code
          Corp ("we," "our," or "us"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of
          Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our
          services.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Description of Services</h2>
        <p>
          Hana Code Corp designs, builds, and operates mobile and web
          applications. Our current offerings include:
        </p>
        <div class="features">
          <div class="feature">
            <h3>Slackwater</h3>
            <p>
              A retirement planning application designed specifically for
              Canadians. Slackwater models retirement timelines and optimizes
              withdrawal strategies across RRSP, TFSA, and non-registered
              accounts, incorporating CPP, OAS, and Canadian tax rules.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>
          We may add, modify, or discontinue services at any time. We will
          provide reasonable notice of significant changes where possible.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>User Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>When using our services, you agree to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide accurate and complete information when using our applications</li>
          <li>Use our services only for lawful purposes and in accordance with these terms</li>
          <li>Not attempt to reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble our applications</li>
          <li>Not use our services to infringe on the rights of others</li>
          <li>Keep your account credentials secure if you create an account</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Financial Planning Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Slackwater and any other financial tools we provide are for
          informational and educational purposes only.</strong> They do not
          constitute financial, tax, investment, or legal advice.
        </p>
        <p>
          Retirement projections, withdrawal strategies, and tax estimates are
          based on the information you provide and general assumptions about
          future conditions. Actual results will vary. Tax laws, CPP/OAS rules,
          and account regulations may change.
        </p>
        <p>
          You should consult with a qualified financial advisor, tax
          professional, or other appropriate professional before making financial
          decisions based on information from our applications.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          All content, features, functionality, design, code, and intellectual
          property associated with our applications and services are owned by
          Hana Code Corp and are protected by Canadian and international
          copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may not copy, modify, distribute, sell, or lease any part of our
          services without our written permission.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          Our services are provided "as is" and "as available" without
          warranties of any kind, either express or implied. We do not warrant
          that our services will be uninterrupted, error-free, or completely
          secure.
        </p>
        <p>
          Financial projections and calculations are estimates based on the data
          you provide and are not guarantees of future results.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Hana Code Corp
          shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
          consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits or
          revenues, whether incurred directly or indirectly, or any loss of
          data, use, goodwill, or other intangible losses resulting from your
          use of our services.
        </p>
        <p>
          In no event shall our total liability exceed the amount you have paid
          us in the twelve months preceding the claim.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service shall be governed by and construed in
          accordance with the laws of the Province of Alberta and the federal
          laws of Canada applicable therein. Any disputes arising from these
          terms or your use of our services shall be subject to the exclusive
          jurisdiction of the courts of Alberta, Canada.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may revise these Terms of Service from time to time. When we make
          changes, we will update the "Effective Date" at the top of this page.
          Your continued use of our services after changes are posted
          constitutes your acceptance of the revised terms.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us:
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Hana Code Corp</strong><br />
          Calgary, Alberta, Canada<br />
          <a href="mailto:hana@cousins.ai">hana@cousins.ai</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding-top: 6rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 4rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .effective {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  ul {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  li {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .card {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .card:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .features {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .feature {
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  .feature h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .feature p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero {
      padding-top: 4rem;
      padding-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
